In this article, the White House Office of the Press Secretary announces the proclamation of Columbus Day by President Barack Obama. It highlights the significance of Christopher Columbus's voyages and the impact they had on the world. The article also acknowledges the contributions of indigenous communities and the suffering they endured as a result of the changes brought about by Columbus's expeditions. It mentions that people from all over the world, like Columbus, have come to America seeking refuge or a better life. The article emphasizes the intrepid character and spirit of possibility that defines America. Lastly, it states that the Congress has requested the observance of Columbus Day on the second Monday of October each year, and President Obama has proclaimed October 11, 2010, as Columbus Day.